# CANONIFY - canonical pattern manifest

> Copy this to `CANONIFY.md` at your repo root and fill in the doc summaries. This file is the
> routing manifest for Canonify: the three gates (`/canonify-plan`, `/canonify-build`,
> `/canonify-commit`) read the one-line summaries below to find the right reference doc.

The routing manifest for **Canonify**. Its three gates read this file: **Plan** (`/canonify-plan`
- orient on the whole landscape), **Build** (`/canonify-build` - route a task to the docs it
implicates and load them), and **Commit** (`/canonify-commit` - audit a diff against those same
docs). Scan each one-line summary below against the task (or diff); for every match, load the
matching doc and read it before writing or shipping code.

