## How to use

1. Read this whole file (keep it short on purpose).
2. For each line whose keywords match the task/diff, open that doc and read it.
3. Docs cross-link each other when topics overlap - follow those links.
4. Only after reading the matched docs, write the plan / code, or run the commit audit.

If nothing matches, proceed normally - not every change touches a documented pattern. If a match
feels weak, open it anyway: skim cost is low; rebuilding a pattern wrong is expensive.
